.TH "dspxfr_one_seg" 9 "dspxfr_one_seg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dspxfr_one_seg \- Write a block of data into DSP code or data RAM using pre-allocated DMA engine.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dspxfr_one_seg
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "const struct dsp_image_seg *fls "  ","
.BI "unsigned int reloc "  ","
.BI "struct dma_engine *dma_engine "  ","
.BI "unsigned int dma_chan "  ","
.BI "unsigned int port_map_mask "  ","
.BI "bool ovly "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "fls" 12
pointer to a fast load image
.IP "reloc" 12
Relocation address for loading single-segment overlays, or 0 for
no relocation
.IP "dma_engine" 12
pointer to DMA engine to be used for DSP download
.IP "dma_chan" 12
The number of DMA channels used for DSP download
.IP "port_map_mask" 12
port mapping
.IP "ovly" 12
TRUE if overlay format is required
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns zero or a negative error code.
